TextBody:
Hey Christian,

I've attached your license to this email. Please use the instructions below to update the license file and let me know if that resolved the issue.

Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (formerly Netwrix StealthAUDIT)  
How to download your software:
Download the software from the Netwrix Customer Portal. Not in the portal yet? Learn how to register now. If you cannot see your products in the portal, please email customer.portal@netwrix.com. 
As always, you can get answers to your technical questions at the Netwrix Technical Knowledge Center 
Useful links to the Netwrix website: 

	Netwrix Customer Portal

Use your account to submit and track support tickets, download updates of your software, get product training. 
Not in the portal yet? Learn how to register now. If you cannot see your products in the portal, please email customer.portal@netwrix.com. 


	Netwrix Technical Knowledge Center

Familiarize yourself the online documentation and knowledge base prior to a new installation. 
License Installation – First Time Install:
Follow these steps to import your Netwrix Enterprise Auditor license key file: 
Step 1 – Save the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor license file to the desktop of the machine where Netwrix Enterprise Auditor is installed.
Step 2 – Right click on the license file and go to properties, make sure that the license file is unblocked.
Step 3 – Launch the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor Installer and point to the license file. Complete the installation. 
Step 4 – Run Netwrix Enterprise Auditor and confirm license expiration date by going to Help>About.  

License Installation – Existing Install:
Follow these steps to import your Netwrix Enterprise Auditor license key file into your existing Netwrix Enterprise Auditor installation:
Step 1 – Make sure that all running instances of Netwrix Enterprise Auditor have been ended using task manager.
Step 2 – Save the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor license file to the desktop of the machine where Netwrix Enterprise Auditor is installed.
Step 3 – Right click on the license file and go to properties, make sure that the license file is unblocked.
Step 4 – From Add/Remove programs, right click the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor Installation and choose “Change”. Complete the wizard and point to the new license file.  
Step 5 – Run Netwrix Enterprise Auditor and confirm license expiration date by going to Help>About.   

Feel free to reach out with any additional questions!

Thank you,

Tay Caliguiri
